Crimean shirt
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a long, usu. blue, flannel shirt, a kind of early bush shirt, as part of the early colonial outdoors costume
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. Garibaldi shirt, bluey
